column2: A series of short range, high power military vessals which patrol the outskirts of the fleet to catch attackers before they can penetrate deeper.
A number of trade vessels and container ships which guide what trade can be found out in the expansion zone.
Ships used for the holding of large scale public meetings to convey the opinions of the fleet's population to it's Admiralty.
factory ships Specialised in manufactoring the replacement armor used by the Mobile Shipyards to repair damaged Warships.

A specialized Mobile factory used to fabricate and maintain the delicate framework needed to build the special drives equipped on tunnelers as well as provide a storage area for these ships.  These unwieldy ships are capable of creating FTL wakes or tunnels that allow other ships to travel great distances without the need of using artificial wormholes.  The incredible fragility of the tunneler drive combined with its unpredictable nature when destroyed make ships equipped with them unsuited to combat of any kind.
These are the spaces aboard the fleet's flagship dedicated to the military fleet command.
These ships jump ahead of the fleet to lay the groundwork for its arrival in new sectors of space, making transition to these new regions easier.
These are the various ships given over to religious and political organisations within the fleet.
These are ships repurposed by the fleet to act as the entertainment and cultural heart of the fleet.
A specialised series of ships designed to assist in the reclaimation, reconstruction and conversion of old or abandoned colony ships for constant spaceborne habitation.
These are originally short range vessals designed to perform light levels of industry which have since been jury rigged and overclocked to produce all the industrial goods the fleet needs.
The Equivalent of tugboats equipped with lasers, storage units and manipulating arms to gather the raw materials a fleet needs from the millions of asteroids which exist in any solar system.
Ships designed to produce and store the fuel that the other ships in the fleet require to continue on their long celestial voyage.
Asteroids while also being an excellent way to retrieve resources can also provide the perfect targets for military training Exercises.

These are relatively small shipyards designed to be easily moved with fleets. These maintain ships, rebuild damaged or old ships and construct new vessals using raw materials brought in via asteroids.
These ships were handed over entirely to one of mainkind's oldest guilty pleasures entirely, afterall what improve's a ship crew's morale more than liquid courage?

Colony ships which were lost in deep space during the first expansion or which have been carried here over the decades by refugees and migrants who never settled down have been repurposed to be suitable for prolonged spaceborne habitation.

These were originally colony ships, however as the fleet transitioned to a permanent spaceborne lifestyle these vessals were completely converted to support aquaponics. Aquaponics consists of keeping both live fish together in the same enviroment as plants. This allows for a well rounded diet while also providing the most effiecient use of space possible.
